For me it can be scary bcuz I’m always listening to music in the car.
I’ve had an instance where a song had a pitch that gave me an aura. I had time to stop the car before I went out for a few seconds.

Video games as well. 
That new Sonic game preview that floated around thankfully had a photosensitive warning on it.

I wish more companies would make the effort to identify if their media has these things that can be dangerous for people and to put up proper warnings.

Not posting this for sympathy. Just to educate people so that they can be aware of how mainstream media can be dangerous to those w/ disabilities.
Commercials, movies, tv shows. So many have strobing lights. Dramas & horror movies tend to use high pitch tones for mood as well.

Not many people are aware that #MusicogenicEpilepsy exist.
It’s not just music, it’s also certain tones/pitches that can trigger seizures. Interestingly I have this along with #PhotosensitiveEpilepsy. 
Watching movies these days can be tricky & often trigger FAS seizures for me.
